Try to fix the relative import problem

From previous commit, it would fail if using command:
pypy [CLY_PATH]/dataPrepScripts/ExtractVariantCandidates.py [options]

python sys.path is without the project directory and interpreted as
"[CLY_PATH]/dataPrepScripts/" but not "[CLY_PATH]"
So any relative import inside dataPrepScripts/Clair folders would fail.

reference:
https://chrisyeh96.github.io/2017/08/08/definitive-guide-python-imports.html

Now trying to use clair.py as centralized location,
the downside is now the command would become:
pypy [CLY_PATH]/clair.py ExtractVariantCandidates [options]
